\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. Q. trojana} Webb in Loudon,{\i  Gard. Mag.} ({\i Loudon}) {\b 15:} 590 (1839) ({\i Q. macedonica} DC.). Semi-evergreen or deciduous tree up to 15 m; young twigs puberulent. Leaves 3-7(-10) cm, obovate-oblong, sinuate-dentate with 8-14 pairs of mucronate or subaristate teeth, shining and subglabrous on both surfaces when mature; petiole 2-5 mm. Fruit ripening in the second year; involucre with lowest scales appressed, the middle ones deflexed and the upper erect or incurved.{\i  Balkan peninsula} ({\i mainly in the west});{\i  S.E. Italy}. Al Bu Gr It Ju Tu.
