\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 11. Q. petraea} (Mattuschka) Liebl., {\i Fl. Fuld.} 403 (1784) ({\i Q. sessiliflora} Salisb., {\i Q. sessilis} Ehrh., {\i Q. dshorochensis} C. Koch). Deciduous tree up to 40 m; twigs glabrous. Leaves 7-12 cm, obovate, cuneate at the base, very finely appressed-hairy beneath, and with persistent tufts of brownish hairs in the vein-axils, sinuately lobed with 5-8 pairs of rounded lobes; intercalary veins often present; petiole 18-25 mm. Scales of involucre ovate-lanceolate, thin, not tuberculate, pubescent. 2n = 24.{\i  Forming often pure woods, usually on somewhat poor soils. W., C. & S.E. Europe, southwards to C. Spain and S. Albania, northwards to 60° N. in Norway}. Al Au Be Br Bu Co Cz Da Ga Ge Hb He Ho Hs Hu It Ju No Po Rm Rs(B, C, W, K, E) Si Su Tu.
